The paper analyzes the journal structure in the China Scientific and Technical Papers and Citations Database (CSTPCD) and compares it with the Science Citation Index. This involves analyzing citation relations between journals, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on scientific publications and their hierarchies suggests a connection to digital libraries (cs.DL). The mention of different fields of science and their varying international visibility suggests a connection to scientific computing (cs.SC) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
